FBIS4-38916 "drsov107_t_94010" FBIS-SOV-94-107 Daily Report 2 Jun 1994 BALTIC STATES Estonia New Justice Minister Appointed New Justice Minister Appointed WS0206140494 Tallinn BNS in English 1014 GMT 2 Jun 94 WS0206140494 Tallinn BNS English BFN [Text] Tallinn, June 02, BNS -- President Lennart Meri today appointed Urmas Arumae as the new justice minister, the president's office told BNS. Arumae's candidacy was put forward earlier this morning by Prime Minister Mart Laar. Arumae, 37, is a graduate of the Faculty of Law of Tartu University. He later graduated from the Estonian Higher School of Commerce and obtained his master's degree in international business management at the University of San Francisco. After a stint as a vice president of Silves Enterprises Ltd., he established his own legal aid company, Concordia. Arumae is also president of the Estonian Lawyers Union.
